	<Title>
		Recipe: Guacamole
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		This version of guacamole uses the traditional avocado plus beans for added fiber and protein. It&apos;s great as a dip or as a spread for sandwiches or wraps.
	</Abstract>
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		8
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip">
		&lt;p&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Dietitian&apos;s tip:&lt;/strong&gt; This easy dish is great as a dip or a spread for sandwiches or wraps. 
&lt;/p&gt;
	</DietitianTip>
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;
In a medium bowl, mix avocado, beans, cumin, lime juice and cayenne pepper. Add chopped tomato and shallot and stir to combine. Serve. 
&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 avocado, diced (about 1/2 cup)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/2 cup canned beans (black or pinto), drained and rinsed&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2 teaspoons ground cumin&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Juice of 1 lime (about 2 tablespoons)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/4 teaspoon cayenne, chipotle or ancho chili powder (optional)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 large ripe tomato, diced (about 1 cup)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 shallot, minced (about 1/4 cup)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
	</Ingredients>
